  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , a new divergence measure called the Jensen-Renyi divergence was introduced as a generalization of the Jensen-Shannon divergence being based on Renyi Entropy [CITATION_2] . In contrast to the JS divergence used earlier [CITATION_3] , the exponential order of Renyi entropy as well as the weights to control the measurement sensitivity of the probability densities can be adjusted in JR divergence. Further, the JR divergence measure enjoys appealing mathematical properties such as convexity and symmetry, affording a great flexibility in a number of applications [CITATION_4] . Finally, a related work by Chiang et al. [CITATION_5] has used JR divergence for pairwise image matching where contiguity constraints between pixels could be utilized.",
